    <h2>Football Blog</h2>

    <p>
      American football is a strategic, high-contact team sport played with an oval ball, 
      where two teams of 11 players aim to score points by advancing to the opponent’s end zone.
      Known as "football" in the US, it is a game of territory and precision.
    </p>

    <h3>Definition</h3>
    <p>
      American football is a game similar to rugby that is played by two teams of eleven players using an oval-shaped ball.
    </p>

    <h3>Objective</h3>
    <p>
      The main goal is to advance the ball down a field (100 yards long) into the opposing team’s end zone to score a touchdown.
    </p>

    <h3>Gameplay</h3>
    <p>
      Teams have four attempts (called "downs") to advance at least 10 yards. 
      If they succeed, they get a new set of downs. If not, they must surrender the ball.
    </p>

    <h3>Components</h3>
    <p>
      It is a highly tactical sport focusing on physical contact, strategy, and specialized roles.
    </p>

    <h3>Key League</h3>
    <p>
      The highest professional level is the National Football League (NFL), played in the United States.
    </p>

    <h3>Key Vocabulary</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Touchdown:</strong> 6 points</li>
      <li><strong>Field Goal:</strong> 3 points</li>
      <li><strong>Downs:</strong> Attempts</li>
      <li><strong>End zone:</strong> Scoring area</li>
      <li><strong>Kickoff:</strong> Start of play</li>
    </ul>

